You are in the master bedroom of the farm house. Two end tables stand either side of a magnificent four-poster bed, taking centre stage in this sparsely decorated, yet confortable room. On the tables sit matching ornate lamps. Across on the opposite wall from the bed hangs an odd choice of painting: It appears to be some sort of modern art, all brilliant white and straight lines. It's certainly at odds with the rest of the house. A second door leads out from this room.
