You're standing in a fairly small bedroom. The bunk beds in the corner and the posters adorning the walls indicate this bedroom belongs to the children of whichever family lives here. Judging by the duvet on the top bunk, this belongs to a boy for sure - dinosaurs appear to be attacking some sort of transforming robot on the art work. The bottom bunk you can't be sure about, with its plain purple bed spread and its white pillow.

There's something weird about this room that you can't put your finger on. It feels 'new' somehow, as if it was recently built and furnished, and the room seems too large for the space it occupies. Probably not important, you think, as you shake the feeling off.
You can go east.

> x top bunk

> x top bunk
The vivid depiction of dinosaurs vs robots on the duvet cover really stands out. Whoever sleeps here sure likes adventure!
A lump in the middle of the duvet, barely perceptable, indicates something hiding beneath.
