> use coin on metal box
You take the coin from your pocket and hold it over the recess in the box lid. Dropping it in place, you see it's a perfect fit. How the magpie outside the farm ended up with it you may never know, but that doesn't matter now: With a barely audible click, the box lid swings open, released as if from a spring.

Inside the box, placed on a velvet cushion, is a closed locket. Possibly a gift for the lady of the house?
