Inside, the stables are still fairly intact. There are half a dozen stocks for keeping animals separated, with bits of straw still lining most of them despite the asbsence of any actual livestock. A wrought iron bracket for holding farm tools is fastened across the length of one wall.

There are two doorways in and out of this place: To the east you can see the ruined farm buildings you passed earlier, and a much larger exit leads out, way off to the west, where the path stops at a small farm house in the distance.
