You're standing by a fallen dry stone wall, once designed to keep trespassers out of what was probably a working farm. Several crumbling buildings are dotted across the landscape, their doors long since rotted away and their windows home to staccato shards of mouldy glass. A worn path, little more than a trail of dirt, snakes across to a stable over the way. The long grass grabs at your ankles as you move off the path to look around the area, and you almost trip over an ancient, round millstone buried within the green velt.

To the northwest, the trail splits off, heading to a silo beyond - apart from the stable to the west, it's the only other building here you'd feel safe exploring.
You can go east, west or northwest.

