You are inside an empty grain silo. Corrugated steel walls stretch up high above you, meeting in a conical roof some ninety feet up. Despite the horror stories you've heard about people drowning in grain, there appears to be some sort of ledge above the door you entered by designed for human access, although you have no idea why anyone would want to be up there looking down at tons of grain.

In the centre of the room is a large hole, where the grain would filter into an auger to be transported.

The only other thing you see here is a baled bundle of hay.
