You've arrived at the source of the river. Layers of stone lie rugged before you; a hidden spring somewhere underground struggles against these natural formations, causing the steady stream to flow and meander through the valley. The water here is fresh and free of silt and mud. It's as clear as any you've ever seen. A pair of blue plastic barrels lie by the edge of the water.
You can go southeast.

