You are hopping from rock to rock following the river as it runs downhill, trying as best you can to keep your feet dry. Eventually you can't follow it any further as it becomes too rocky and dangerous, but you can reach the north bank from here. You'll have to follow the river back up stream to get to land on the southern side however, as there's nothing on the south bank here except nasty looking rocks. A pair of blue plastic barrels lie by the edge of the water.
